    "Furthermore, [CGV25] shows that community recovery is possible above the threshold (2) using m-clique counting when q ≍ n -2/(m+1), for m ∈ {3, 4, 5,.",
    "}, and by counting self-avoiding paths of length m -1 when q ≍ n -(m-2)/(m-1), for m ∈ {3, 4, 5,.",
    "For the remaining density regimes, Conjecture 1.4 of [CGV25] predicts that community recovery remains possible above the threshold (2) through the enumeration of specific motifs satisfying certain structural properties.",
    "The present paper is a follow-up to [CGV25], dedicated to proving this conjecture.",
    "Our main contributions are:"
